Vice President Biden has announced Dr. Colin Kahl as his new National Security Advisor. Dr. Kahl is currently an associate professor at Georgetown University and has experience as a Senior Fellow and Director of the Middle East Security Program at the Center for a New American Security. He has also served as Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for the Middle East. Dr. Kahl's expertise in national security issues, particularly in the Middle East, makes him a valuable addition to the team. His formal title will be Deputy Assistant to the President and National Security Advisor to the Vice President.